articles.description: Payton Pritchard had 19 points and 10 assists, and Troy Brown Jr. also had a double-double to lead Oregon past Washington State 84-57 on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Pritchard, Brown lead Oregon to 84-57 win over Washington St

articles.description: Shep Garner scored 16 points and Tony Carr had 15 points to lead Penn State to a 74-52 victory over Illinois on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Garner, Carr help Penn State beat Illinois 74-52

articles.description: After scoring a team-high 23 points, Grayson Allen credits the good ball movement to set him up in the Blue Devils' 80-69 win over the Yellow Jackets.
articles.headline: Allen credits ball movement for open looks

articles.description: Grayson Allen scored 23 points and No. 9 Duke beat Georgia Tech 80-69 on Sunday night to end a two-game losing streak.

articles.description: Devin Davis scored 16 points, Armoni Brooks had a double-double and Houston throttled Tulane 73-42 on Sunday to stay in a tie for second place in the American Athletic Conference standings with Wichita State.
articles.headline: Houston dissects cold-shooting Tulane 73-42

videos.description: Oshae Brissett hits from range to tie the game up against Kansas.
videos.headline: Brissett drains triple for Syracuse

videos.description: Devonte' Graham throws a perfect pass to Udoka Azubuike for the Jayhawks slam dunk.
videos.headline: Graham lobs up it up to Azubuike

videos.description: Sviatoslav Mykhailiuk banks in a three and then swishes another for the Jayhawks.
videos.headline: Mykhailiuk hits back-to-back triples

videos.description: Devonte' Graham lobs it up from the top of the key to a cutting Sviatoslav Mykhailiuk to extend the Kansas lead.
videos.headline: Graham hits Mykhailiuk for the alley-oop

videos.description: Syracuse's Pascal Chukwu blunders an easy slam dunk and then gets a technical foul for hanging on the rim.
videos.headline: Chukwu makes missed dunk worse with technical

videos.description: Udoka Azubuike throws down the dunk as Kansas works the lob to perfection again.
videos.headline: It's Lob City for the Jayhawks

videos.description: Syracuse's Frank Howard scores through the contact for the tough layup.
videos.headline: Howard scores tough and-1 lay-in

videos.description: Lagerald Vick shows off some bounce with a sweet alley-oop.
videos.headline: Vick throws down another lob for Jayhawks

videos.description: Tyus Battle hammers home a slam dunk to give some juice to the Orange offense.
videos.headline: Battle throws down the tomahawk

videos.description: Devonte' Graham uses a nice step-back jumper to get open for his sixth triple of the game.
videos.headline: Graham nails big three

videos.description: Lagerald Vick makes a nice one-handed catch and then punishes the rim as Kansas continues their barrage of alley-oops.
videos.headline: Vick reaches back for a vicious slam

videos.description: Mitch Lightfoot gets in on the Lob City fun for the Jayhawks.
videos.headline: Kansas continues their Clippers impression

videos.description: Dick Vitale and Rich Hollenberg talk with Devonte' Graham after he dropped a career-high 35 points against Syracuse.
videos.headline: Graham scores career-high, talks with Vitale
